trend_summary: Imagery shows gradual suburban consolidation. Small forest clearings fill with detached-house subdivisions, mainly southwest and mid-corridor. The eastern industrial/airport zone gains extra warehouses and paved yards. Highway alignment stays, but junctions and one roundabout are upgraded. Despite these additions, broad woodland belts, ponds and wetlands are largely retained, so growth is moderate.
notable_changes: New cul-de-sac housing pockets carved out of forest in the southwest sector.
Residential infill between existing curved streets in the central neighbourhood.
Expansion of warehouse blocks and paved lots adjacent to the airport/industrial estate in the east.
Construction of a small roundabout or upgraded junction on the main arterial road.
Clearing of vegetation along the pond edge followed by managed wetland appearance.
